The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are core topics in computer science and economics. The use of linear/convex programming and polytopes suggests a connection to optimization and computational geometry, which are also common in CS. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also involves the manipulation of large amounts of data, which could place it in the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of optimization techniques and algorithms for implementation suggest a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
